标题

GPU-Kernel -Prefix Copy

题目描述

Given a dynamically sized array of floats called input, remove all elements that are equal to 0.0. The remaining non-zero values should be placed at the beginning of a new array output. The order of non-zero elements in output does not need to match their original order in input.​
Return two results:​
  1. output：The output array, with all non-zero elements placed at the front.​
  1. output_size: The number of non-zero elements (i.e., the number of valid elements in output).​
Note: The remaining part of the output array (after the non-zero elements) can be ignored.​

Exmaple:​
// Input:​
input = [0.0, 3.2, 0.0, -1.1, 5.0]​
input_size = 5​
// Output:​
output = [3.2, -1.1, 5.0, ..., ...] // Non-zero values placed at the front​
output_size = 3 // Number of non-zero elements​

Parameter Descriptions:​
  • input: The original input array (located in device memory).​
  • output: The output array used to store non-zero elements (also in device memory).​
  • input_size: The size of the input array.​
  • output_size: A pointer to a device-side integer used to record the number of non-zero elements.​

__global__ void move_to_prefix_kernel(​
  • const float* input, ​
  • int* input_size, ​
  • float* output, ​
  • int* output_size) {​
